# CRUD Patterns (Inboxes reference implementation)

## Controller

- `before_action :set_resource` for all member actions
- On failure: `render :new/:edit, status: :unprocessable_entity`; re-populate any collection ivars needed by the form (e.g. `@tags`)
- On success: `redirect_to @resource, notice: "Resource was successfully created/updated."`
- Private `set_resource` (finds by `params[:id]`) and `resource_params` (strong params)
- For JSON columns: expose virtual `*_text` attributes; populate in `new`/`edit` via a private `populate_json_text_fields` helper using `JSON.pretty_generate`
- Modal actions: GET `*_modal` renders the modal view; PATCH `mark_*` performs the update (render modal on failure with `status: :unprocessable_entity`)
- Bulk actions: separate `bulk_*_modal` (GET, renders modal) and `bulk_*` (PATCH, redirects with notice) endpoints

```ruby
# ✅ GOOD
def create
  @inbox = Inbox.new(inbox_params)
  if @inbox.save
    redirect_to @inbox, notice: "Inbox was successfully created."
  else
    @tags = Tag.order(:name)
    render :new, status: :unprocessable_entity
  end
end
```

## Index View

- Root: `<div data-controller="keyboard-shortcuts">`
- Inline help overlay: `data-keyboard-shortcuts-target="help"` with `data-action="click->keyboard-shortcuts#closeHelp"`, toggled via `?` button or `keyboard-shortcuts#toggleHelp`
- Render `'header'` and `'filter_tabs'` partials at the top
- List content wrapper: `data-controller="bulk-actions list-navigation"` with URL value attributes for bulk endpoints
- Render `'bulk_actions'` partial (select-all + bulk action buttons)
- Default: list (table), optional grid via `?view=grid`
- Rows/cards: `data-list-navigation-target="row"`; View links: `data: { list_navigation_view: true }`
- Bulk select: `data-bulk-actions-target="checkbox"`, `data-action="change->bulk-actions#updateActions"`
- Empty state: centered SVG + `<h3>` + `<p>`; grid uses `rounded-lg border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 py-16`, list uses `py-16` inside the table card
- End of template: `<turbo-frame id="modal"></turbo-frame>`

### Header partial (`_header.html.erb`)

- Title + subtitle; action row on the right
- Filters toggle + sort dropdown: both use `data-controller="disclosure"` with `data-disclosure-target="panel"`
- Preserve query params (filter, sort, direction, source, query, view) when navigating
- Primary CTA (New): `rounded-md bg-gray-900 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white` with `n` shortcut
- Help toggle button: `data-action="click->keyboard-shortcuts#toggleHelp"`

### Filter tabs partial (`_filter_tabs.html.erb`)

- Pill tabs with counts; active tab: `bg-gray-900 text-white`, inactive: `text-gray-600 hover:bg-gray-100`
- Search form: `data-controller="search-form"`, `data-turbo-action="replace"`, preserve other params via hidden inputs
- List/grid toggle: icon buttons, active state `border-gray-400 bg-gray-100`

### Bulk actions partial (`_bulk_actions.html.erb`)

- Bar: `rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white px-4 py-2.5 shadow-sm`
- Select-all: `data-bulk-actions-target="selectAll"`, `data-action="change->bulk-actions#selectAll"`
- Action buttons: `data-bulk-actions-target="actionButton"`, disabled until selection; include keyboard shortcut hints
- Context-aware actions (e.g. Archive vs Unarchive based on current filter)

## Show View

- Root: `<div data-controller="keyboard-shortcuts">` with inline help overlay
- Header row (`mb-8 flex items-center justify-between`):
  - Left: breadcrumb back link with `u` shortcut (`← Parent / Title`)
  - Right: contextual action buttons (Process, Tag, Archive/Unarchive) + divider + Edit (`e`) + Delete (`d`, danger style) + `?` help button
  - Modal actions: `data: { turbo_frame: 'modal', keyboard_shortcuts_target: "trigger", keyboard_shortcuts_key: "…" }`
  - Destructive confirms: `form: { data: { turbo_confirm: "…" } }`
- Details card: section header (`border-b border-gray-100 bg-gray-50 px-6 py-3`) + `<dl class="divide-y divide-gray-100">` with `<div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-4 px-6 py-4">` rows (`dt` + `dd class="col-span-2"`)
- JSON display: side-by-side cards in `grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2`, each with section header + `<pre class="overflow-auto rounded-md bg-gray-50 p-4 font-mono text-xs text-gray-800 leading-relaxed max-h-80">`
- End: `<turbo-frame id="modal"></turbo-frame>`

## New / Edit Views

- Both wrap in `data-controller="keyboard-shortcuts"`
- Breadcrumb back-link (`mb-8 flex items-center gap-x-3`): `← Parent / Title` with `u` shortcut; new links to index, edit links to show
- Render form inside: `<div class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 bg-white p-6 shadow-sm">`

## Form Partial

Error banner (always first):
```erb
<% if resource.errors.any? %>
  <div class="rounded-md bg-red-50 border border-red-200 p-4">
    <div class="flex">
      <!-- SVG icon -->
      <div class="ml-3">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-medium text-red-800">
          <%= pluralize(resource.errors.count, 'error') %> prevented this … from being saved:
        </h3>
        <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5 text-sm text-red-700">
          <% resource.errors.full_messages.each do |msg| %><li><%= msg %></li><% end %>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
<% end %>
```

- Form root: `form_with(model: resource, class: "space-y-6")`
- Label class: `block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1`
- Standard input class:
```
block w-full rounded-md border border-gray-300 px-3 py-2 text-sm text-gray-900 placeholder-gray-400 shadow-sm focus:border-indigo-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-1 focus:ring-indigo-500
```
- JSON text areas: add `font-mono`, `spellcheck: false`; side-by-side in `grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 lg:grid-cols-2`; helper text below each field
- Basic fields: two-column grid `grid grid-cols-1 gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2` where appropriate

Submit row:
```
inline-flex items-center gap-x-1.5 justify-center rounded-md bg-indigo-600 px-4 py-2 text-sm font-semibold text-white shadow-sm hover:bg-indigo-500 focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-indigo-600 transition-colors duration-150 cursor-pointer
```

- Submit label: `resource.persisted? ? 'Update …' : 'Create …'`
- Submit shortcut: `data: { keyboard_shortcuts_target: "trigger", keyboard_shortcuts_key: "Enter" }`
- Cancel link: `resource.persisted? ? resource : resources_path`, class `text-sm font-medium text-gray-600 hover:text-gray-900`

## Modal Views (Turbo Frame)

- Wrapped in `<turbo-frame id="modal">`
- Full-screen overlay: `fixed inset-0 z-50 flex items-center justify-center` + backdrop `bg-gray-500/75`
- Dialog panel: `relative z-10 w-full max-w-md rounded-xl bg-white shadow-2xl` with `data-controller="modal"`
- Header: title + close link (`data: { turbo_frame: 'modal' }`) + descriptive subtitle
- Form: `data: { turbo_frame: '_top' }` so success redirects the full page
- Cancel: `data: { turbo_frame: 'modal', modal_target: 'cancel' }`
- Submit: `data: { modal_target: 'submit' }`
- Empty-state warning: `rounded-md bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200` when required collection is empty

